<title type="html"><![CDATA[Recording music directly from NES to MP3.  Please help.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8961&amp;p=94893#p94893"><![CDATA[
Seems like a different NES might be worth a try, or buying the original NES power adapter. I myself ran into very hideous sound by using a universal adapter...increasing the voltage from 9 to 12 improved the situation immensely, though I dunno if 12 is good for the NES' electronic chain.<br /><br />If you're gonna go to the trouble of recording an NES, I would suggest FLAC as a compressed audio format. Mp3 is fine only if you know what you're doing (i.e., the latest version of LAME is not the best version) and intend on keeping the original wav. Also, soundcard quality and recording level are immensely important...try to record at 24-bit if your system allows it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4439">cak</a> — Fri Jun 01, 2012 4:57 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
