<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8961&amp;p=94871#p94871"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Recording music directly from NES to MP3.  Please help.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8961&amp;p=94871#p94871"><![CDATA[
Even if you use the yellow and red A/V jacks, some of the video signal still leaks into the audio. You can minimize this by making the video signal as weak as possible. Have your music player turn the screen off and set the background color to $0D while recording.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">  ; turn off rendering<br />  ldx #$00<br />  stx $2001<br /><br />  ; set background color<br />  lda #$3F<br />  sta $2006<br />  stx $2006<br />  lda #$0D<br />  sta $2007<br /><br />  ; exit palette-setting mode<br />  stx $2006<br />  stx $2006</div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu May 31, 2012 1:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
